Preheat oven to 325 degrees F. Mix crumbs, butter, sugar and cinnamon. Press firmly onto bottom and 1 inch up side of 9-inch springform pan. Bake 10 min. or until lightly browned. Cool on wire rack. Combine caramels, cream and coffee granules in large microwavable bowl. Microwave on MEDIUM 2 to 3 min. or until caramels are completely melted, stirring every min. Stir in pecans. Spread caramel mixture evenly over crust. Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm. Drizzle with melted chocolate. Cut into 12 slices to serve. Store leftover tart in refrigerator.